         <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>Would you recommend pet tanking at 45?  </P><P>Root-rotting seem to work fine outside on the regular Plagebone singles, but the pairs inside the thieves pyramid kinda prevent that.</P><P>Any suggestions?</P><P>Gunkk<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>I haven't tried meleeing inside since pulling with a spell results in a single pull (at least at level 46). I pull with dooming darkness, wait until it is outside then send in the pet and fear. They usually drop just as dooming finishes, so thats a kill every 90 seconds.</P><P>Sure you can do it faster, but this way I end of full mana (CoBoned) after each fight, and faster would not be better since I still have to wait a couple of minutes for them to repop once I've cleared the room.</P><P>The only things that reduces my mana is the odd level 8 ward undead spell that I throw at it to raise me evoc.</P><P>Oh - this is also a good spot to practice your 'beguile undead' skills.</P><P>Rhys (Xatan, 46 Iksar Necro, Antonius Bayle)<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=236573" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=236573</a><BR>All trade, no twink.</P><P>Edited by - rhys on 08/19/2002  07:14:17<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
