         <BR>Some comments about the Plaguebone Thieves camp in DL.</P><P>You *can* pet-tank at level 45.  I could easily hold the entire camp with this method at 46.  I used Shackle of Spirit, Pact, Vamp Curse, Leach, Shadow Vortex and Wave of Enfeeblement (remember this one?), Harmshield (never used) and FD (used when getting trained by quadders).  I found this faster, and more mana-efficient than fear kiting.</P><P>It's a very popular spot on Nameless.  That's why I'd recommend pet-tanking over fear kiting.  If you chase the mobs East down the ruins, someone eventually will show up and steal your camp using the "Oh, sorry... didn't see you there" line.  Had to convince more than one visitor that "Really, the ENTIRE camp is taken."  Once I got it cleared, most folks would see the room was constantly empty and move on.  </P><P>Besides the obvious training, a common camp-stealing tactic is for quadders to run over the top (or back side) of the pyramid and proximity aggro the mobs inside without you seeing 'em run by.  Only time I had to deal with it, he wasn't very good at quadding, and died WITHOUT my help.  Heh! <img src=icon_smile_big.gif border=0 align=middle> </P><P></P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310159" target="_blank">Gunkk</a><BR>46 Iksar Necro<BR>The Nameless<BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

